4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a new embedding of fracture surfaces to simultaneously compute both closing and opening morphological operations, which involves designing efficient data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the least likely category, but it is possible that the paper may have some relevance to cryptography and security in the context of archaeological artifact authentication.
